
For @out[ch]@@"m"@ of canvas, you need to pay @price[ch]@ dinars. If @"x"@ denotes the length of the canvas and @"y"@ the corresponding price, the coefficient of proportionality @"k"@ in the function 
@center@ @"y = k * x"@ @hspacept(8)@ is @hspacept(8)@ @"k = "@@lib.check_number(coef, 40)@. 
Complete the table that shows how much needs to be paid for the given lengths of canvas. 
@center@ @mycanvas()@
How much does @out[sig1]@@"m"@ of canvas cost? 
@center@  @lib.check_number(price[sig1], 40)@ dinars;
How many meters of canvas can be purchased for @price[sig2]@ dinars? 
@center@  @lib.check_number(out[sig2], 20)@@"m"@. 
            